00814 // Surface mamagement functions
00815 BOOLEAN LoadAnimationSurface( UINT16 usSoldierID, UINT16 usSurfaceIndex, UINT16 usAnimState )
00816 {
00817       AuxObjectData *pAuxData;
00818 
00819       // Check for valid surface
00820       CHECKF( usSurfaceIndex < NUMANIMATIONSURFACETYPES );
00821 
00822       // Check if surface is loaded
00823       if ( gAnimSurfaceDatabase[ usSurfaceIndex ].hVideoObject != NULL )
00824       {
00825             // just increment usage counter ( below )
00826             AnimDebugMsg( String( "Surface Database: Hit %d", usSurfaceIndex ) );
00827 
00828       }
00829       else
00830       {
00831             // Load into memory
00832             VOBJECT_DESC                              VObjectDesc;
00833             HVOBJECT                                        hVObject;
00834             HIMAGE                                                hImage;
00835             CHAR8                                                 sFilename[48];
00836             STRUCTURE_FILE_REF            *pStructureFileRef;
00837 
00838             AnimDebugMsg( String( "Surface Database: Loading %d", usSurfaceIndex ) );
00839 
00840             sprintf( (char *)gSystemDebugStr, "Cache Load" );
00841 
00842         // Create video object
00843             FilenameForBPP(gAnimSurfaceDatabase[ usSurfaceIndex ].Filename, sFilename);
00844             hImage = CreateImage(/*gAnimSurfaceDatabase[ usSurfaceIndex ].Filename*/sFilename, IMAGE_ALLDATA );
00845 
00846         if (hImage == NULL)
00847         {
00848                    return( SET_ERROR( "Error: Could not load animation file %s", sFilename ) );
00849         }
00850 
00851             VObjectDesc.fCreateFlags = VOBJECT_CREATE_FROMHIMAGE;
00852             VObjectDesc.hImage = hImage;
00853 
00854             hVObject = CreateVideoObject( &VObjectDesc );
00855 
00856             if ( hVObject == NULL )
00857             {
00858                   // Report error
00859                   SET_ERROR( "Could not load animation file: %s", gAnimSurfaceDatabase[ usSurfaceIndex ].Filename );
00860                   // Video Object will set error conition.]
00861                   DestroyImage( hImage );
00862                   return( FALSE );
00863             }
00864 
00865             // Get aux data
00866             if (hImage->uiAppDataSize == hVObject->usNumberOfObjects * sizeof( AuxObjectData ))
00867             {
00868                   // Valid auxiliary data, so get # od frames from data
00869                   pAuxData = ( AuxObjectData* ) hImage->pAppData;
00870 
00871                   gAnimSurfaceDatabase[ usSurfaceIndex ].uiNumFramesPerDir = pAuxData->ubNumberOfFrames;                
00872 
00873             }
00874             else
00875             {
00876                   // Report error
00877                   SET_ERROR( "Invalid # of animations given" );
00878                   DestroyImage( hImage );
00879                   return( FALSE );
00880             }
00881 
00882             // get structure data if any
00883             pStructureFileRef = InternalGetAnimationStructureRef( usSoldierID, usSurfaceIndex, usAnimState, TRUE );
00884 
00885             if ( pStructureFileRef != NULL )
00886             {
00887                   INT16 sStartFrame = 0;
00888 
00889                   if ( usSurfaceIndex == RGMPRONE )
00890                   {
00891                         sStartFrame = 5;
00892                   }
00893                   else if ( usSurfaceIndex >= QUEENMONSTERSTANDING && usSurfaceIndex <= QUEENMONSTERSWIPE )
00894                   {
00895                         sStartFrame = -1;
00896                   }
00897 
00898                   if (AddZStripInfoToVObject( hVObject, pStructureFileRef, TRUE, sStartFrame ) == FALSE)
00899                   {
00900                         DestroyImage( hImage );
00901                         DeleteVideoObject( hVObject );
00902                         SET_ERROR(  "Animation structure ZStrip creation error: %s", sFilename );
00903                         return( FALSE );
00904                   }
00905                   
00906             }
00907 
00908         // the hImage is no longer needed
00909         DestroyImage( hImage );
00910 
00911             // Set video object index
00912             gAnimSurfaceDatabase[ usSurfaceIndex ].hVideoObject = hVObject;
00913 
00914             // Determine if we have a problem with #frames + directions ( ie mismatch )
00915             if (  ( gAnimSurfaceDatabase[ usSurfaceIndex ].uiNumDirections * gAnimSurfaceDatabase[ usSurfaceIndex ].uiNumFramesPerDir ) != gAnimSurfaceDatabase[ usSurfaceIndex ].hVideoObject->usNumberOfObjects )
00916             {
00917                   AnimDebugMsg( String( "Surface Database: WARNING!!! Surface %d has #frames mismatch.", usSurfaceIndex ) );
00918             }
00919       }
00920 
00921       // Increment usage count only if history for soldier is not yet set
00922       if ( gbAnimUsageHistory[ usSurfaceIndex ][ usSoldierID ] == 0 )
00923       {
00924             AnimDebugMsg( String( "Surface Database: Incrementing Usage %d ( Soldier %d )", usSurfaceIndex, usSoldierID ) );
00925             // Increment usage count
00926             gAnimSurfaceDatabase[ usSurfaceIndex ].bUsageCount++; 
00927             // Set history for particular sodlier
00928             gbAnimUsageHistory[ usSurfaceIndex ][ usSoldierID ]++;
00929 
00930       }
00931 
00932       return( TRUE );
00933 }

00936 BOOLEAN UnLoadAnimationSurface( UINT16 usSoldierID, UINT16 usSurfaceIndex )
00937 {
00938       // Decrement usage flag, only if this soldier has it currently tagged
00939       if ( gbAnimUsageHistory[ usSurfaceIndex ][ usSoldierID ] > 0 )
00940       {
00941             // Decrement usage count
00942             AnimDebugMsg( String( "Surface Database: Decrementing Usage %d ( Soldier %d )", usSurfaceIndex, usSoldierID ) );
00943             gAnimSurfaceDatabase[ usSurfaceIndex ].bUsageCount--; 
00944             // Set history for particular sodlier
00945             gbAnimUsageHistory[ usSurfaceIndex ][ usSoldierID ] = 0;
00946 
00947       }
00948       else
00949       {
00950             // Return warning that we have not actually loaded the surface previously
00951             AnimDebugMsg( String( "Surface Database: WARNING!!! Soldier has tried to unlock surface that he has not locked." ) );
00952             return( FALSE );
00953       }
00954 
00955       AnimDebugMsg( String( "Surface Database: MercUsage: %d, Global Uasage: %d", gbAnimUsageHistory[ usSurfaceIndex ][ usSoldierID ], gAnimSurfaceDatabase[ usSurfaceIndex ].bUsageCount ) );
00956 
00957       // Check for < 0
00958       if ( gAnimSurfaceDatabase[ usSurfaceIndex ].bUsageCount < 0 )
00959       {
00960             gAnimSurfaceDatabase[ usSurfaceIndex ].bUsageCount = 0;
00961       }
00962 
00963 
00964       // Check if count has reached zero and delet if so
00965       if ( gAnimSurfaceDatabase[ usSurfaceIndex ].bUsageCount == 0 )
00966       {
00967       AnimDebugMsg( String( "Surface Database: Unloading Surface: %d", usSurfaceIndex ) );
00968 
00969               CHECKF( gAnimSurfaceDatabase[ usSurfaceIndex ].hVideoObject != NULL )
00970 
00971                   DeleteVideoObject( gAnimSurfaceDatabase[ usSurfaceIndex ].hVideoObject );
00972                   gAnimSurfaceDatabase[ usSurfaceIndex ].hVideoObject = NULL;
00973       }
00974 
00975       return( TRUE );
00976 
00977 }
